## Bug 1: Database Password Environment Variable Missing

### Exact Runtime Error

```text
terminate called after throwing an instance of 'std::runtime_error'
  what():  CRAWLER_DB_PASSWORD environment variable is not set
```

### Context

After building the project, I ran:

```bash
./build/crawler.exe
```

The program terminated before crawling started.

The `Crawler` class contains a `PageStorage` object. When a `Crawler` object is created, its member objects are also constructed.

```text
main()
   |
   v
Crawler crawler(maxDepth)
   |
   v
PageStorage Constructor
   |
   v
Read CRAWLER_DB_PASSWORD
   |
   v
Environment variable missing
   |
   v
Runtime Error
```

The `PageStorage` constructor expects the MySQL password through:

```text
CRAWLER_DB_PASSWORD
```

### Resolution

The password must be available in the active terminal:

```bash
export CRAWLER_DB_PASSWORD="your_password"
```

The value can be checked using:

```bash
echo $CRAWLER_DB_PASSWORD
```

This error showed that integration can introduce constructor-level dependencies. The crawler cannot even start if one of its required member components fails during construction.

