## Bug 4: Linker Failure After Updating `main.cpp`

After modifying `main.cpp`, the project was rebuilt:

```bash
cmake --build .
```

The build produced:

```text
[ 10%] Built target CollectionsLib
[ 12%] Building CXX object CMakeFiles/Crawler.dir/main.cpp.obj
[ 15%] Linking CXX executable Crawler.exe
collect2.exe: error: ld returned 1 exit status
mingw32-make[2]: *** [CMakeFiles\Crawler.dir\build.make:291: Crawler.exe] Error 1
mingw32-make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles\Makefile2:198: CMakeFiles/Crawler.dir/all] Error 2
mingw32-make: *** [Makefile:135: all] Error 2
```

The important observation was:

```text
Building CXX object CMakeFiles/Crawler.dir/main.cpp.obj
```

completed successfully.

The failure occurred during:

```text
Linking CXX executable Crawler.exe
```

Therefore, this was a linker error rather than a normal C++ syntax error.

The final line:

```text
collect2.exe: error: ld returned 1 exit status
```

does not provide the actual root cause.

The useful error usually appears before this line.

The next debugging command is:

```bash
cmake --build . --verbose
```

This should reveal whether the actual problem is:

```text
undefined reference
missing source file
missing implementation
missing library
incorrect linker configuration
```

