# Section 3 — Memory Diagram

The main architectural change today was creating the `Crawler` controller.

```text
+------------------------------------------------+
|                    Crawler                     |
|------------------------------------------------|
| int maxDepth                                   |
|                                                |
| URLNormalizer normalizer                       |
| SeenStorage seenstorage                        |
| URLFrontier frontier                           |
| Fetcher fetcher                                |
| FrameworkDetector frameworkDetector            |
| RenderEngine renderEngine                      |
| PageStorage pageStorage                        |
| HTMLParser htmlParser                          |
+------------------------------------------------+
```

The complete integrated flow is:

```text
                    Seed URL
                       |
                       v
                URLValidator
                       |
                       v
                URLNormalizer
                       |
                       v
                 SeenStorage
                       |
                       v
                 URLFrontier
                       |
                       v
                    Fetcher
                       |
                       v
                  FetchResult
                       |
                       v
              FrameworkDetector
                       |
             +---------+---------+
             |                   |
             v                   v
        Static HTML         JS Framework
             |                   |
             |                   v
             |              RenderEngine
             |                   |
             +---------+---------+
                       |
                       v
                   finalHTML
                       |
                       v
                  PageStorage
                       |
                       v
                   HTMLParser
                       |
                       v
                Extracted Links
                       |
                       v
              Validate + Normalize
                       |
                       v
                 SeenStorage
                       |
                       v
                 URLFrontier
                       |
                       v
                     Repeat
```

Each URL is represented using:

```cpp
struct URLNode {
  std::string url;
  int depth;
  int retryCount;
};
```

Example:

```text
+------------------------------------+
| URLNode                            |
|------------------------------------|
| url        = https://example.com   |
| depth      = 1                     |
| retryCount = 0                     |
+------------------------------------+
```

Depth progression:

```text
Seed URL
Depth 0
   |
   +------> URL A
   |        Depth 1
   |
   +------> URL B
            Depth 1
               |
               +------> URL C
                        Depth 2
```

The crawler stores:

```cpp
int maxDepth;
```

while every `URLNode` stores its own:

```cpp
int depth;
```

If:

```cpp
currentNode.depth >= maxDepth
```

the current page can still be stored, but its links are not added to the frontier.

