# Section 4 — Code Reference

**Commit Hash:** `[Add commit hash after commit]`

**Suggested Commit Message:**

```text
feat: integrate crawler components into complete crawling pipeline
```

**Primary File:** `src/crawler.cpp`  
**Header File:** `include/crawler.h`  
**Relevant Lines:** `[Add final line numbers after commit]`

The central crawler integration follows this structure:

```cpp
Crawler::Crawler(int maxDepth) : maxDepth(maxDepth) {}
```

The seed URL is first validated:

```cpp
if (!URLValidator::isValid(seedURL)) {
  return;
}
```

It is then normalized:

```cpp
std::string normalizedURL = normalizer.normalize(seedURL);
```

Duplicate URLs are rejected:

```cpp
if (!seenstorage.addSeenURL(normalizedURL)) {
  return;
}
```

The initial node is created:

```cpp
URLNode seedNode(normalizedURL, 0, 0);
frontier.addURL(seedNode);
```

The crawler processes URLs until the frontier becomes empty:

```cpp
while (!frontier.isEmpty()) {
  URLNode currentNode = frontier.getNextURL();
```

The page is fetched:

```cpp
FetchResult result = fetcher.fetch(currentNode.url);

if (!result.success) {
  continue;
}
```

The framework is detected:

```cpp
FrameworkType framework =
    frameworkDetector.detect(result);
```

The fetched HTML is used by default:

```cpp
std::string finalHTML = result.html;
```

For non-static pages, the render engine is used:

```cpp
if (framework != FrameworkType::STATIC_HTML) {

  if (!renderEngine.createTab(currentNode.url)) {
    continue;
  }

  if (!renderEngine.connect()) {
    continue;
  }

  if (!renderEngine.navigate(currentNode.url)) {
    renderEngine.disconnect();
    continue;
  }

  finalHTML = renderEngine.getRenderedHTML();

  renderEngine.disconnect();
}
```

The final HTML is stored:

```cpp
if (!pageStorage.storePage(
        currentNode.url,
        finalHTML,
        currentNode.depth)) {
  continue;
}
```

Before extracting more links, the depth is checked:

```cpp
if (currentNode.depth >= maxDepth) {
  continue;
}
```

Links are extracted:

```cpp
std::vector<std::string> extractedLinks =
    htmlParser.extractLinks(
        finalHTML,
        currentNode.url
    );
```

Each extracted URL follows:

```text
Validate
   |
   v
Normalize
   |
   v
Duplicate Check
   |
   v
Create URLNode
   |
   v
Add to Frontier
```

The implementation is:

```cpp
for (const std::string &link : extractedLinks) {

  if (!URLValidator::isValid(link)) {
    continue;
  }

  std::string normalizedLink =
      normalizer.normalize(link);

  if (!seenstorage.addSeenURL(normalizedLink)) {
    continue;
  }

  URLNode newNode(
      normalizedLink,
      currentNode.depth + 1,
      0
  );

  frontier.addURL(newNode);
}
```

This completes the first integrated crawler loop.

